<div class="comment-text">
<p>“Siegel refers to the old “refrigerator mother” controversy here” Indeed. Bettelheim belongs to the distant past, and is hardly relevant to any contemporary discussion of autism.</p>
<p>But even apart from antique Freudian-flavored theories of autism, it seems unquestionable that the diagnosis itself has changed, as in Bettelheim’s day a diagnosis of “autistic” was limited to those with deficits so severe as to be disabling in most everyday social environments.</p>
