<div class="comment-text">
<p>Please don’t misinterpret my comment. The reality of hundreds of thousands of children diagnosed with a lifelong disability is no mirage. It is real, new and profoundly worrisome. The notion that “nurture” in the form of homicidal mothers was the cause was a bizarre Freudian construct that has been widely rejected. We are left only with biological causation and environmental causes (there’s no such thing as a genetic epidemic). </p>
<p>That said, while a generation of disabled children growing into permanently disabled adults, our largely progressive medical establishment stands paralyzed in denial of any real problem. The industry is not guilty of making up the disorder, but rather stands happy to accept payments for service when the real issue is getting to the biological cause(s) of the epidemic and stopping them</p>
