<p>I suspect a large portion of the increase in ASD diagnoses is simply a result of better diagnosis.  (There’s been some suggestion that the concentration of high-functioning aspies in places like silicon valley may have led to a genuine increase in incidence, at least on a localised level, but it hasn’t withstood scrutiny very well.)</p>
